      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>dill</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>crème fraîche </strong>to a bowl with<strong> </strong>your <strong>wholegrain</strong> <strong>mustard </strong>(not a mustard fan? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, most of the <strong>chopped dill</strong> (save some for garnish!) and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and mix it all together – this is your <strong>creamy mustard sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
